562
00:39:35,292 --> 00:39:36,585
About what?

563
00:39:40,214 --> 00:39:42,007
About what happened.

564
00:39:42,549 --> 00:39:43,550
When?

565
00:39:44,259 --> 00:39:45,761
When I got hurt.

566
00:39:46,220 --> 00:39:48,180
What else did I tell you?

567
00:39:49,139 --> 00:39:52,059
You said that if I told what Mommy did...

568
00:39:52,768 --> 00:39:56,021
...the judge and the nice people
will protect me...

569
00:39:56,271 --> 00:39:58,857
...and Mommy wouldn't hurt me anymore.

570
00:39:59,608 --> 00:40:01,568
Do you think you can do that?

571
00:40:01,652 --> 00:40:03,862
Answer my questions in court?

572
00:40:04,571 --> 00:40:06,865
And tell what Mommy did to you?

573
00:40:09,868 --> 00:40:11,537
I think you can.

574
00:40:11,912 --> 00:40:13,705
Mommy will be there.

575
00:40:14,706 --> 00:40:17,793
She can't hurt you.
She can't even talk to you.

576
00:40:18,460 --> 00:40:20,462
You'll be completely safe.

577
00:40:23,006 --> 00:40:24,383
You promise?

578
00:40:26,176 --> 00:40:27,553
I promise.

579
00:40:36,270 --> 00:40:38,021
His father got to him last night.

580
00:40:38,105 --> 00:40:41,275
Told him God would put him in hell
if he testified against his mother.

581
00:40:41,358 --> 00:40:42,442
He's terrified.

582
00:40:42,526 --> 00:40:45,904
If you're not ready, we'll ask the judge
for a couple more days.

583
00:40:45,988 --> 00:40:46,989
No.

584
00:40:47,114 --> 00:40:49,783
We've got to do it now
or we'll lose him for good.

585
00:40:49,867 --> 00:40:53,203
Your mommy took you to the hospital
because you were hurt.

586
00:40:53,745 --> 00:40:55,706
What part of you was hurt?

587
00:40:56,373 --> 00:40:57,541
My head.

588
00:40:58,542 --> 00:41:00,210
How was it hurt?

589
00:41:04,673 --> 00:41:07,217
Wendell, how did you hurt your head?

590
00:41:10,721 --> 00:41:12,389
I don't remember.

591
00:41:16,727 --> 00:41:18,729
Have you ever seen this?

592
00:41:19,271 --> 00:41:20,230
Yes.

593
00:41:20,314 --> 00:41:21,523
Where?

594
00:41:21,899 --> 00:41:23,692
- In the cellar.
- At home?

595
00:41:23,901 --> 00:41:24,902
Yes.

596
00:41:25,068 --> 00:41:27,571
Did somebody put your head inside it?

597
00:41:29,114 --> 00:41:30,365
Wendell?

598
00:41:32,451 --> 00:41:36,079
What did you say when somebody
put your head in the vise?

599
00:41:37,414 --> 00:41:41,335
You told me you screamed
when your head was put in the vise.

600
00:41:42,669 --> 00:41:43,879
Remember?

601
00:41:44,505 --> 00:41:45,756
You told me.

602
00:41:48,842 --> 00:41:50,219
"I promise...

603
00:41:50,385 --> 00:41:51,970
"...l'll be a good boy.

604
00:41:52,054 --> 00:41:53,764
"I'll be a good boy."

605
00:41:54,681 --> 00:41:56,517
Did somebody answer?

606
00:41:58,769 --> 00:41:59,978
Mommy.

607
00:42:00,229 --> 00:42:03,440
Mommy said I was a bad boy
and I deserved to die.

608
00:42:04,066 --> 00:42:06,109
And then what did Mommy do?

609
00:42:06,819 --> 00:42:09,071
She made it tighter and tighter.

610
00:42:09,154 --> 00:42:10,614
On your head?

611
00:42:10,823 --> 00:42:13,617
She hurt my head.
My mommy hurt my head.

612
00:42:15,786 --> 00:42:17,871
No further questions, Your Honor.

613
00:42:17,955 --> 00:42:20,082
The doctors have told us...

614
00:42:20,332 --> 00:42:21,959
...that the wounds...

615
00:42:22,042 --> 00:42:25,337
...that Wendell suffered
could not have come from a fall...

616
00:42:25,420 --> 00:42:27,965
...as the defense would have you believe.

617
00:42:28,924 --> 00:42:32,803
The police told us they found a vise
at the home of the defendant.

618
00:42:33,720 --> 00:42:35,931
Medical experts have testified...

619
00:42:36,098 --> 00:42:39,518
...that the size and the shape
of the jaws of that vise...

620
00:42:39,643 --> 00:42:44,606
...exactly match the size and the shape
of the wounds to the little boy's head.

621
00:42:45,023 --> 00:42:47,317
And this evidence is clear...

622
00:42:47,818 --> 00:42:49,486
...and uncontested.

623
00:42:51,363 --> 00:42:54,199
But the most compelling evidence
in this trial...

624
00:42:54,283 --> 00:42:57,077
...comes not from doctors,
or police officers...

625
00:42:57,286 --> 00:42:59,496
...or other expert witnesses.

626
00:42:59,663 --> 00:43:01,832
The most damning testimony...

627
00:43:02,291 --> 00:43:05,252
...comes from an abused
and frightened child...

628
00:43:05,544 --> 00:43:08,422
...who overcame his fear and his pain...

629
00:43:09,131 --> 00:43:11,717
...to tell you, in his own words...

630
00:43:12,509 --> 00:43:14,511
...what really happened.

631
00:43:15,762 --> 00:43:20,017
If you're to remember nothing else
as you begin your deliberations...

632
00:43:20,100 --> 00:43:22,102
...remember Wendell's words:

633
00:43:22,978 --> 00:43:25,022
"My mommy hurt my head."

634
00:43:26,690 --> 00:43:28,734
"My mommy hurt my head."

635
00:43:33,155 --> 00:43:35,199
"My mommy hurt my head."

636
00:44:13,654 --> 00:44:15,239
Congratulations.

637
00:44:21,245 --> 00:44:23,163
It's gonna be so good.

638
00:47:00,028 --> 00:47:02,197
You're still in love with her.

639
00:47:06,326 --> 00:47:08,036
It was never love.

640
00:47:09,204 --> 00:47:10,873
What was it, then?

641
00:47:17,504 --> 00:47:19,214
It was never love.

642
00:47:22,050 --> 00:47:24,887
What did she have
to make you feel so much?

643
00:47:37,232 --> 00:47:39,067
Ladies and gentlemen...

644
00:47:39,485 --> 00:47:41,236
...Raymond Horgan.

645
00:47:56,960 --> 00:47:58,795
Thank you. Thank you.

646
00:48:00,923 --> 00:48:03,050
I wanted to come down
and say a few words...

647
00:48:03,133 --> 00:48:07,429
...before I call Mr. Della Guardia
and congratulate him on his victory.

648
00:48:08,514 --> 00:48:10,098
No, no, no. Come on.

649
00:48:11,475 --> 00:48:15,270
Of all the wonderful things
that have happened to me in 12 years...

650
00:48:16,063 --> 00:48:17,940
...the best has been...

651
00:48:18,649 --> 00:48:21,276
...knowing and working with all ofyou.

652
00:48:22,236 --> 00:48:24,822
Wait till you hear what's going down.
It's strange.

653
00:48:24,905 --> 00:48:28,075
Someone's fucked up over at the Hall.
It's way wrong.

654
00:48:28,158 --> 00:48:29,868
- Why?
- I get a message.

655
00:48:29,952 --> 00:48:34,039
I'm supposed to be in the chief's office
8:00 tomorrow to be interviewed.

656
00:48:34,122 --> 00:48:35,123
By Molto.

657
00:48:35,207 --> 00:48:37,167
No discussion. Interview.

658
00:48:37,251 --> 00:48:38,836
It's like they're after me, right?

659
00:48:38,919 --> 00:48:41,213
Another thing. When I came back tonight...

660
00:48:41,296 --> 00:48:44,800
...they took all the receipts
of the evidence I inventoried on Polhemus.

661
00:48:44,883 --> 00:48:46,635
No questions asked.

662
00:48:47,177 --> 00:48:48,679
