that all county employees get printed.

697
00:50:55,764 --> 00:50:57,266
This is absurd.

698
00:50:57,891 --> 00:51:00,936
The phone records
you told Lipranzer not to get?

699
00:51:01,061 --> 00:51:03,313
We had the phone company
pull them this morning.

700
00:51:03,397 --> 00:51:05,357
You were calling her all month.

701
00:51:05,440 --> 00:51:08,443
There's a call from your house
to hers that night.

702
00:51:14,199 --> 00:51:16,118
My God, you're serious.

703
00:51:20,205 --> 00:51:21,957
Tommy, for Christ's sake!

704
00:51:22,166 --> 00:51:23,208
Sabich.

705
00:51:23,959 --> 00:51:26,086
I want you to know one thing. I know.

706
00:51:26,170 --> 00:51:27,087
Sure you do.

707
00:51:27,171 --> 00:51:29,298
Go ahead, play cool. I know.

708
00:51:29,423 --> 00:51:31,758
You killed her. You're the guy.

709
00:51:32,759 --> 00:51:33,760
Oh, yeah?

710
00:51:33,844 --> 00:51:36,763
Yeah, you're right. You're always right.

711
00:51:43,645 --> 00:51:46,815
They think I killed her.
They're going to charge me.

712
00:51:47,691 --> 00:51:50,819
Don't be seen with me, man.
They'll fucking bury you.

713
00:51:53,989 --> 00:51:56,783
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to scare you.

714
00:51:58,660 --> 00:52:00,162
Are you sick?

715
00:52:03,749 --> 00:52:07,169
Nico and Molto are charging me
with Carolyn's murder.

716
00:52:09,963 --> 00:52:13,592
They found my fingerprints
on a glass of beer in her apartment.

717
00:52:17,596 --> 00:52:19,097
What does this mean?

718
00:52:19,223 --> 00:52:21,266
Grand jury investigation.

719
00:52:22,643 --> 00:52:26,438
They will or they won't indict me.
If they do, there'll be a trial.

720
00:52:29,316 --> 00:52:31,527
It's not going to go that far.

721
00:52:34,696 --> 00:52:36,865
I'm going to need a lawyer.

722
00:52:39,201 --> 00:52:41,870
A very, very good lawyer.
Expensive lawyer.

723
00:52:45,707 --> 00:52:47,876
It could break us financially.

724
00:52:49,169 --> 00:52:51,213
We can mortgage the house.

725
00:52:52,214 --> 00:52:54,049
Or sell it if we have to.

726
00:52:57,302 --> 00:52:59,221
What time does Nat get home?

727
00:53:00,889 --> 00:53:01,932
Nat?

728
00:53:04,893 --> 00:53:06,103
Oh, Rusty!

729
00:53:19,700 --> 00:53:22,703
A lot ofpeople think Raymond
shouldn't run again.

730
00:53:23,537 --> 00:53:28,542
If he agrees to step aside, the party
will let him decide who will take his place.

731
00:53:30,544 --> 00:53:33,005
They know he won't hand it all to Nico.

732
00:53:33,088 --> 00:53:34,548
That's for sure.

733
00:53:36,216 --> 00:53:37,885
Who would he choose?

734
00:53:39,761 --> 00:53:41,513
Somebody from the office.

735
00:53:42,514 --> 00:53:44,391
Carry on his traditions.

736
00:53:44,558 --> 00:53:45,559
You?

737
00:53:49,938 --> 00:53:51,356
Mac, maybe.

738
00:53:52,691 --> 00:53:55,360
She'd make a great candidate,
in that wheelchair.

739
00:53:55,444 --> 00:53:57,946
That chair is not very telegenic.

740
00:53:59,990 --> 00:54:01,700
I think he'd pick you.

741
00:54:04,203 --> 00:54:05,913
You're the natural.

742
00:54:12,169 --> 00:54:13,212
Rusty...

743
00:54:13,337 --> 00:54:16,256
...if you let him know you want it,
it'll be you.

744
00:54:17,257 --> 00:54:19,885
I should just tell Raymond his time is up?

745
00:54:20,093 --> 00:54:21,929
- You could be tactful.
- No.

746
00:54:23,013 --> 00:54:24,223
Why not?

747
00:54:25,432 --> 00:54:27,601
I'm not going to bite that hand.

748
00:54:28,018 --> 00:54:30,437
If Raymond wants out, that's up to him.

749
00:54:30,771 --> 00:54:34,233
He's still the best candidate around,
against Della Guardia.

750
00:54:34,483 --> 00:54:37,444
Without Raymond,
Nico doesn't have an issue.

751
00:54:37,820 --> 00:54:41,657
Pull the party's people and Raymond's
people together behind somebody else...

752
00:54:41,740 --> 00:54:44,701
