754
00:54:55,629 --> 00:54:57,798
You've thought a lot about this.

755
00:54:58,549 --> 00:55:00,425
He just needs a push.

756
00:55:04,012 --> 00:55:06,431
Push him yourself. It's not in me.

757
00:55:12,896 --> 00:55:13,856
What?

758
00:55:14,606 --> 00:55:17,401
Were you all set on being chief deputy?

759
00:55:19,278 --> 00:55:20,362
Carolyn...

760
00:55:22,447 --> 00:55:26,076
...if I can get away tonight
shall I get some take-out?

761
00:55:27,077 --> 00:55:29,746
I like you, Rusty, but I think it's over.

762
00:55:30,831 --> 00:55:33,458
It's just not right for me now. It's over.

763
00:55:33,542 --> 00:55:35,252
I don't accept that.

764
00:55:35,460 --> 00:55:37,045
You don't accept it?

765
00:55:37,171 --> 00:55:38,672
Do I have a say?

766
00:55:41,216 --> 00:55:43,343
I don't want us to end up enemies.

767
00:55:51,810 --> 00:55:53,854
Mac said it was all right.

768
00:55:54,229 --> 00:55:55,689
Have it your way.

769
00:55:58,942 --> 00:56:00,694
Someone's in my office.

770
00:56:02,654 --> 00:56:03,864
What is it, Rusty?

771
00:56:03,947 --> 00:56:06,867
I wanted to talk about this rapist
you habitualized.

772
00:56:06,950 --> 00:56:08,577
There's some problems.

773
00:56:09,453 --> 00:56:11,371
I'm late for an appointment.

774
00:56:11,580 --> 00:56:14,875
I would appreciate it
if you could put it in a memo.

775
00:56:15,501 --> 00:56:17,044
You keep avoiding me.

776
00:56:17,127 --> 00:56:20,714
You communicate through memos.
You skip meetings I'm supposed to go to.

777
00:56:20,797 --> 00:56:22,466
It's affecting work.

778
00:56:22,549 --> 00:56:23,675
My work?

779
00:56:24,843 --> 00:56:26,053
My work.

780
00:56:27,221 --> 00:56:29,556
I tried to make it easier for you.

781
00:56:32,643 --> 00:56:34,728
You make me feel uncomfortable.

782
00:56:34,812 --> 00:56:37,981
I just want to be with you.
Can't we just talk about it?

783
00:56:39,650 --> 00:56:42,027
I'm involved with someone else.

784
00:56:43,111 --> 00:56:44,404
Since when?

785
00:56:44,905 --> 00:56:46,907
What is it you want from me?

786
00:56:48,784 --> 00:56:50,410
What do I have to do?

787
00:56:52,663 --> 00:56:53,747
Grow up.

788
00:57:31,660 --> 00:57:33,203
Rozat K. Sabich?

789
00:57:35,664 --> 00:57:37,583
Rusty, I don't like to be here.

790
00:57:37,666 --> 00:57:39,918
A search warrant for these premises.

791
00:57:42,796 --> 00:57:44,131
Come on in.

792
00:58:00,898 --> 00:58:03,400
They're taking swatches from your suits.

793
00:58:03,650 --> 00:58:06,820
They'll try to match threads
from my clothing and the carpet...

794
00:58:06,904 --> 00:58:09,740
...with fibers they might find
at her apartment.

795
00:58:09,823 --> 00:58:12,326
They're not looking for a murder weapon?

796
00:58:12,409 --> 00:58:14,578
I wouldn't be stupid enough
to bring it home.

797
00:58:14,661 --> 00:58:18,832
If they look for it and don't find it,
they'll have to admit that in court.

798
00:58:19,333 --> 00:58:21,668
I'll have to give a blood sample.

799
00:58:22,127 --> 00:58:23,504
If you refuse?

800
00:58:24,046 --> 00:58:25,839
They've got a warrant.

801
00:58:26,006 --> 00:58:27,633
It's all routine.

802
00:58:28,842 --> 00:58:31,678
I'm going to ask Sandy Stern
to take my case.

803
00:58:37,684 --> 00:58:39,019
Hi, Sandy.

804
00:58:46,443 --> 00:58:50,280
I realize you would like to avoid
public places at a time like this...

805
00:58:50,364 --> 00:58:53,951
...but I don't think it is wise
for you to go into hiding.

806
00:58:55,118 --> 00:58:58,497
I'm flattered that you want me
to represent you in this case.

807
00:58:58,580 --> 00:59:01,208
You have been my toughest adversary.

808
00:59:03,168 --> 00:59:06,129
Did you get my subpoena
from the grand jury?

809
00:59:06,296 --> 00:59:09,299
This morning.
Clearly, we will not let you testify.

810
00:59:11,218 --> 00:59:14,388
Sandy, you expect me
to take the Fifth Amendment?

811
00:59:14,721 --> 00:59:16,056
Of course.

812
00:59:17,891 --> 00:59:19,309
That I cannot do.

813
00:59:20,894 --> 00:59:25,107
You don't want to prepare the prosecutor
by giving him pretrial statements.

814
00:59:25,190 --> 00:59:28,902
Sandy, I don't think this case
is ever going to go to trial.

815
00:59:29,653 --> 00:59:33,073
If I take the Fifth and refuse to testify
before the grand jury...

816
00:59:33,157 --> 00:59:35,325
...it could destroy my reputation.

817
00:59:37,995 --> 00:59:40,247
The results of the blood tests
have come back.

818
00:59:40,330 --> 00:59:43,959
They have identified you as someone
who secretes A-type antibodies...

819
00:59:44,042 --> 00:59:47,421
...just like the man who had last been
with Ms. Polhemus.

820
00:59:47,754 --> 00:59:50,757
Chances of this being a coincidence
are one in ten.

821
00:59:50,883 --> 00:59:54,928
So, I believe you will be charged
and that you will go to trial.

822
00:59:55,095 --> 00:59:59,766
Have you anything to tell this grand jury
about the death of Carolyn Polhemus?

823
01:00:00,058 --> 01:00:02,769
On the advice of counsel,
I decline to answer.

824
01:00:03,020 --> 01:00:07,399
Wouldn't it be fair to say you were rather
well acquainted with Ms. Polhemus?

825
01:00:07,608 --> 01:00:09,902
On the advice of counsel,
I decline to answer.

826
01:00:09,985 --> 01:00:12,779
Weren't you, in fact,
intimate with the lady?

827
01:00:14,281 --> 01:00:16,992
On the advice of counsel,
I decline to answer.

828
01:00:18,035 --> 01:00:21,246
You are under arrest.
"You have the right to remain silent.

829
01:00:21,330 --> 01:00:24,333
"Anything you say can and will
be used against you.

830
01:00:24,541 --> 01:00:28,128
"You have the right to have a lawyer
present during questioning.

831
01:00:28,587 --> 01:00:32,508
"If you cannot hire a lawyer,
one will be appointed to represent you.

832
01:00:34,593 --> 01:00:37,429
"You may stop answering questions
at any time."

833
01:00:37,554 --> 01:00:40,224
Do you understand the rights
I have explained to you?

834
01:00:40,307 --> 01:00:42,392
Call Sandy Stern to make bail.

835
01:00:56,990 --> 01:00:58,992
Sandy should be available in a few hours.

836
01:00:59,076 --> 01:01:00,994
Let's see what they got.

837
01:01:01,829 --> 01:01:04,164
Can't believe there could be
any more surprises.

838
01:01:04,248 --> 01:01:07,584
That's when they come.
That's why they're called surprises.

839
01:01:11,421 --> 01:01:13,924
Do we now understand
Della Guardia's case?

840
01:01:15,342 --> 01:01:16,844
Yes, I think I do.

841
01:01:18,095 --> 01:01:19,596
Let me hear it.

842
01:01:23,517 --> 01:01:25,853
Sabich is obsessed with Polhemus.

843
01:01:26,520 --> 01:01:28,689
She ditches him for another man.

844
01:01:29,189 --> 01:01:31,024
Sabich becomes enraged.

845
01:01:31,108 --> 01:01:32,693
He can't let go.

846
01:01:33,360 --> 01:01:35,529
One night, knowing his wife is out...

847
01:01:35,612 --> 01:01:38,365
...he calls her and begs her
to see him again.

848
01:01:38,949 --> 01:01:40,951
Carolyn finally agrees.

849
01:01:42,119 --> 01:01:45,038
She rolls around with him
for auld lang syne.

850
01:01:45,330 --> 01:01:46,832
Then something goes wrong.

851
01:01:46,915 --> 01:01:50,377
Sabich is jealous. He wants more
than she's willing to give.

852
01:01:51,044 --> 01:01:52,254
He blows it.

853
01:01:52,337 --> 01:01:55,048
Gives her what for
with some heavy instrument.

854
01:01:55,257 --> 01:01:57,593
Decides to make it look like rape.

855
01:01:57,926 --> 01:02:01,763
Sabich is a prosecutor,
knows there'll be dozens of suspects.

856
01:02:02,556 --> 01:02:03,891
He ties her up.

857
01:02:03,974 --> 01:02:07,394
Opens the latches to make it look
like someone slipped in.

858
01:02:08,729 --> 01:02:10,981
And this is the diabolical part...

859
01:02:11,773 --> 01:02:14,651
...pulls out her diaphragm
so it looks like rape.

860
01:02:14,943 --> 01:02:18,030
But in his haste and confusion,
he makes mistakes.

861
01:02:18,780 --> 01:02:20,991
He forgets the glass he drank from.

862
01:02:21,158 --> 01:02:25,287
He doesn't think the forensic chemist
will be able to ID the spermicide.

863
01:02:26,079 --> 01:02:28,582
But we know he did evil to this woman...

864
01:02:28,790 --> 01:02:33,295
...because he lied about his presence
in her apartment the night she was killed.

865
01:02:33,795 --> 01:02:35,923
His fingerprints on the glass...

866
01:02:36,006 --> 01:02:38,675
...his blood type A identified from semen...

867
01:02:39,176 --> 01:02:43,055
...fibers from the carpets in his home,
tell us he was there.

868
01:02:45,098 --> 01:02:46,767
Very convincing.

869
01:02:48,936 --> 01:02:51,271
But their evidence of motive is weak.

870
01:02:51,355 --> 01:02:53,440
That's where we must attack.

871
01:02:53,899 --> 01:02:58,070
Is there any proof of prior
amorous relationship between the two?

872
01:02:58,320 --> 01:02:59,404
A few telephone calls.

873
01:02:59,488 --> 01:03:01,615
They can be accounted for
by business needs.

874
01:03:01,698 --> 01:03:02,950
- Any diary?
- No.

875
01:03:03,700 --> 01:03:06,745
No note that came with flowers?
No lovers' correspondence?

876
01:03:06,829 --> 01:03:07,996
- No.
- Good.

877
01:03:08,080 --> 01:03:09,665
Gossip will not be admitted.

878
01:03:09,748 --> 01:03:13,752
There are calls from my home to Carolyn's
in October of last year.

879
01:03:13,919 --> 01:03:16,880
You were trying the case
of Wendell McGaffney then.

880
01:03:17,172 --> 01:03:18,924
Reason enough for calling her.

881
01:03:19,007 --> 01:03:22,344
Why did I tell Lipranzer not to get
my home phone records?

882
01:03:22,427 --> 01:03:25,806
I take it for granted that a person
of an innocent state of mind...

883
01:03:25,889 --> 01:03:27,933
...would rule himself out as a suspect...

884
01:03:28,016 --> 01:03:31,019
...and save a busy detective
from wasting time.

885
01:03:32,354 --> 01:03:36,275
Clearly, they hope to win the case
on the strength of their physical evidence.

886
01:03:36,358 --> 01:03:39,403
I'd like to look at that glass.
It could help me.

887
01:03:39,486 --> 01:03:41,822
List a motion for production
of physical evidence.

888
01:03:41,905 --> 01:03:44,491
I want an inventory of everything
in that apartment.

889
01:03:44,575 --> 01:03:46,952
Where's the contraceptive jelly...

890
01:03:47,244 --> 01:03:51,039
...the chemist is saying he finds present?
In her medicine cabinet?

891
01:03:51,123 --> 01:03:52,583
I don't know.

892
01:03:55,669 --> 01:03:57,379
I'll hear worse in court.

